text:
98th St. to Madison Ave. from 5th Ave.
1893
Photograph by Brown Brothers
220 West 42nd St.
New York City
NEG # 3/40

East 98th Street, south side, between Madison and Fifth Avenues, showing rural conditions prevailing on the present site of St. Bernard's School (No. 4-12 E. 98th St.).

Fifth Avenue is to the right and runs across the midground; vacant lots being on this side and Central Park on the far side. In the center is a 3-story brick dwelling, No. 1150 Fifth Avenue, situated at the N.E. corner of 96th Street.

This photo was verified with the photographers successors (H. N. Tiemann & Co) and checked with their records of which this is photo No. 94.

September 1894
H. N. Tiemann, Photo
Gift of Urbrock Collection
NEG. #3139
